50|$|It {{opened on}} 26 June 1903 as the Croydon <b>Mental</b> <b>Hospital</b> (Croydon Borough <b>Mental</b> <b>Hospital</b> or Croydon County Borough <b>Mental</b> <b>Hospital).</b> This is reputedly the first {{institution}} {{to be called}} a 'mental hospital' and never appears officially to have been called an asylum. It is recorded as having been a pioneering centre for psychosurgery.|$|R
